    • Method Detail

      • computeSCCs

        public void computeSCCs()
        Description copied from class: SCCComputer
        Compute (non-trivial) strongly connected components (SCCs) and store them. They should be retrieved using SCCComputer.getSCCs(). States in trivial SCCs (those comprising a single state without a self-loop) are also stored. They should be retrieved using SCCComputer.getNotInSCCs(). You will need to to deref all of these afterwards.
        Specified by:
        computeSCCs in class SCCComputer

      • computeSCCs

        public void computeSCCs(JDDNode filter)
                 throws PrismException
        Description copied from class: SCCComputer
        Compute (non-trivial) strongly connected components (SCCs) containing a state from filter and store them. They should be retrieved using SCCComputer.getSCCs(). States in trivial SCCs (those comprising a single state without a self-loop) are also stored. They should be retrieved using SCCComputer.getNotInSCCs(). You will need to to deref all of these afterwards.
        Specified by:
        computeSCCs in class SCCComputer
        Throws:
